name: Tau Ceti g
description:
Tau Ceti is a single star in the constellation Cetus that is spectrally similar to the Sun, although it has only about 78% of the Sun's mass. At a distance of just under 12 light-years (3.7 parsecs) from the Solar System, it is a relatively nearby star and the closest to our sun. 
The star appears stable, with little stellar variation, it has 4 planet orbiting itself  and is metal-deficient.

Tau Ceti g is the nearest planet too Tau Ceti and its a super Earth exoplanet that orbits a G-type star. Its mass is 1.75 Earths, it takes 20 days to complete one orbit of its star, and is 0.133 AU from its star. its hot and unlivible. you may hate the sun out there.
